---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AgeDifferenceCalculator from '../components/AgeDifferenceCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Age Difference Calculator — Compare Ages Between Two People | Clockr"
	description="Calculate the age gap between two people in years, months, and days. Compare birth dates, see total days apart, current ages, and star signs."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="agdc-page">
		<div class="agdc-header">
			<div class="agdc-eyebrow">
				<span class="agdc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="agdc-title">
				<span class="agdc-gradient">Age Difference</span><br />
				<span class="agdc-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="agdc-subtitle">
				Compare the age gap between two people
			</p>
		</div>

		<AgeDifferenceCalculator client:load />

		<section class="agdc-how">
			<h2 class="agdc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="agdc-how-card">
				<p>
					People calculate age differences for all sorts of reasons — curiosity
					about a partner or friend, figuring out the gap between siblings,
					comparing historical figures who lived in different eras, or exploring
					generational differences between parents and children. Enter two birth
					dates and Clockr shows exactly how far apart they are in years, months,
					and days, along with each person&apos;s current age for context.
				</p>
				<p>
					The calculation works through the calendar step by step rather than
					simply subtracting birth years. Months vary in length — February has
					28 or 29 days while others have 30 or 31 — and leap years add an extra
					day every four years. Clockr accounts for all of this when measuring the
					gap between two dates, giving you a precise breakdown instead of a
					rough estimate based on year numbers alone.
				</p>
				<p>
					Age gaps are just numbers. Whether the difference is a few months or
					several decades, this tool is here for curiosity and practical
					purposes — planning celebrations, settling a friendly debate, or
					learning something new. It is not meant to judge relationships or
					people; every age difference is simply a fact on the calendar.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="agdc-faq">
			<h2 class="agdc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="agdc-faq-list">
				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>How do I calculate the age difference between two people?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter each person&apos;s birth date in the fields above. Clockr
							instantly compares the two dates and shows the gap in years, months,
							and days, along with the total number of days between them. You can
							also add optional names so the result reads naturally — for
							example, &ldquo;Alex is 5 years, 3 months, 12 days older than
							Jordan.&rdquo;
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>What is considered a big age gap in a relationship?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							There is no universal answer — what feels significant varies widely
							by culture, context, and the individuals involved. Some couples
							with a decade or more between them never think twice about it;
							others notice smaller differences. Age gaps are a personal matter,
							and this calculator simply shows the numbers if you are curious.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>How do I find out how many years apart my siblings are?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter each sibling&apos;s birth date as Person 1 and Person 2. The
							result shows the exact gap in years, months, and days — useful when
							siblings were born close together and you want more than a rounded
							year count. Add their names in the optional fields for a
							personalised result.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>Can this calculator compare ages of historical figures?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Enter any two birth dates from history — for example, comparing
							two scientists, artists, or political leaders. The calculator works
							the same way regardless of era, accounting for leap years across
							centuries. Note that very old dates may rely on historical calendar
							conventions that differ from the modern Gregorian calendar.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>How is age difference calculated in years, months, and days?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr starts from the earlier birth date and counts forward through
							full calendar years, then remaining months, then remaining days.
							When a day subtraction would go negative, it borrows from the month
							count using the actual length of the preceding month. This produces
							a human-readable breakdown that matches how we naturally describe
							age gaps.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="agdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="agdc-faq-question"
						>Does birth year alone give an accurate age difference?</summary
					>
					<div class="agdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Not always. Two people born in 1990 and 1995 are roughly five years
							apart, but the exact gap depends on their birth months and days.
							Someone born in December 1990 and March 1995 is about four years and
							three months apart, not a full five years. This calculator uses
							complete birth dates for an accurate result.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="agdc-related">
			<h3 class="agdc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="agdc-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="agdc-related-card"
					><span class="agdc-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/anniversary-calculator" class="agdc-related-card"
					><span class="agdc-related-name">Anniversary Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="agdc-related-card"
					><span class="agdc-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="agdc-related-card"
					><span class="agdc-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.agdc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.agdc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.agdc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.agdc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.agdc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.agdc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.agdc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.agdc-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-dates-row) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 24px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-person) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.agdc-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.agdc-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.agdc-input--text) {
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	:global(.agdc-input::placeholder) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	:global(.agdc-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.agdc-presets) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-presets-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-presets-grid) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-preset) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.agdc-preset:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.agdc-results) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.agdc-main) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-main-heading) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1.5px;
		line-height: 1.15;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-total-days) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.agdc-ages) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-age-card) {
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 16px 14px;
	}

	:global(.agdc-age-text) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.agdc-age-text strong) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	:global(.agdc-zodiac) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.18);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 12px 14px;
	}

	.agdc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.agdc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.agdc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.agdc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.agdc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.agdc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.agdc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.agdc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.agdc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.agdc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.agdc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.agdc-faq-item[open] .agdc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.agdc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.agdc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.agdc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.agdc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.agdc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.agdc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.agdc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.agdc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.agdc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.agdc-dates-row) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		:global(.agdc-main-heading) {
			font-size: 28px;
		}

		:global(.agdc-presets-grid) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		:global(.agdc-ages) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.agdc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
